  "history": {
    "en": "The Dikkulak is a rare, regional landrace from eastern Turkey, primarily found in rural Anatolia. Its name translates to 'prick ear' in Turkish, distinguishing it by its erect ears. Traditionally used for guarding homesteads and controlling vermin, this breed has been shaped by its environment and function rather than formal breeding programs. Not officially recognized by major international kennel clubs.",
    "zh": "迪库拉克犬是土耳其东部罕见的区域性土种犬，主要见于安纳托利亚农村。其名在土耳其语中意为“竖耳”，以其直立耳朵为特征。传统上用于守卫家园和控制害虫，该品种由环境和功能塑造，而非正式繁育计划。未被主要国际犬业俱乐部正式认可。"
  },
